<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-28T08:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-28T08:29:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1954</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Vologda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-28T16:00:00+02:31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 6, 2.32
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>215. <persName corresp="#p_CJK1">Caldwell</persName> telegraphs
                                Soviet government granted him alone privilege of transmitting code
                                messages and requested secrecy thereof, <pb facs="0619" n="545" xml:id="pg_545"/> and he so advised Department. I think
                                acceptance of special privileges unadvisable and recommend
                                Department so instruct <persName corresp="#p_CJK1">Caldwell</persName>. Soviet government industriously
                                endeavoring to create discord between Allies especially America and
                                Japan and should not be encouraged. Please answer.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>